{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/iochannel\/set(buffered:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The buffering state can only be set if the channel’s encoding"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". For any other encoding, the channel must be buffered."}],"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GLib","roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:4GLib17IOChannelProtocolPAAE3set8bufferedySb_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib9IOChannelC","title":"set(buffered:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"buffered","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel\/set(buffered:)"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel\/IOChannelProtocol-Implementations"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"buffered","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A buffered channel can only be set unbuffered if the channel’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"internal buffers have been flushed. Newly created channels or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"channels which have returned "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"eof"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"not require such a flush. For write-only channels, a call to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"g_io_channel_flush () is sufficient. For all other channels,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the buffers may be flushed by a call to g_io_channel_seek_position ().","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This includes the possibility of seeking with seek type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cur"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and an offset of zero. Note that this means that socket-based"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"channels cannot be set unbuffered once they have had data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"read from them.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On unbuffered channels, it is safe to mix read and write","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calls from the new and old APIs, if this is necessary for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"maintaining old code."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The default state of the channel is buffered.","type":"text"}]}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannel":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannel","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOChannel"},{"text":" data type aims to provide a portable method for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"using file descriptors, pipes, and sockets, and integrating them"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"into the main event loop (see [struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"]). Currently,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"full support is available on UNIX platforms; support for Windows","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is only partially complete."}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"IOChannel","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"IOChannel","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOChannel"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","title":"MainContext","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannel/IOChannelProtocol-Implementations":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannel\/iochannelprotocol-implementations","kind":"article","title":"IOChannelProtocol Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel\/IOChannelProtocol-Implementations"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannel/set(buffered:)":{"role":"symbol","title":"set(buffered:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The buffering state can only be set if the channel’s encoding"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"}